## Shape Geometry: Face-Up Area and Finger Coverage

Understanding the face-up area comparison requires understanding each shape's standard L:W ratio.

**Oval at 1.35:1–1.50:1 (standard sweet spot)**

At 1.40:1, a 1ct oval measures approximately 9.0mm × 6.4mm. The ellipse formula gives a face-up area of approximately 42mm². Compared to a 1ct round at 33.2mm², the oval covers **28% more finger surface**. This is the largest face-up coverage of any symmetrical fancy shape at 1ct.

**Pear at 1.50:1–1.65:1 (standard sweet spot)**

At 1.55:1, a 1ct pear measures approximately 9.0mm × 5.8mm — but the pear's asymmetrical footprint (one curved end, one pointed end) means its actual face-up area is less than a full ellipse of the same dimensions. The practical face-up coverage is approximately 36mm², or about **8–12% more than round**. Meaningful, but 14% less than the oval at the same carat weight.

**The face-up reversal:** The oval is larger face-up than the pear despite costing less. This is the direct opposite of the oval vs marquise comparison, where the marquise was larger. In the pear comparison, the oval wins on both price and face-up coverage simultaneously — the pear's premium exists purely for the silhouette, not for size.

| Spec | Oval | Pear |
|---|---|---|
| L:W Sweet Spot | 1.35:1–1.50:1 | 1.50:1–1.65:1 |
| 1ct dimensions | ~9.0mm × 6.4mm | ~9.0mm × 5.8mm |
| Face-up area | ~42mm² | ~36mm² |
| vs Round coverage | +28% | +8–12% |
| Finger elongation | Moderate | Strong (directional) |
| Color minimum (WG/Pt) | G–H | G–H |
| Color minimum (YG) | H–I | H–I |
| Tip protection needed | No | V-prong required |
| Point inspection needed | No | Video audit required |
| Setting orientation | North-South or East-West | Point-up or point-down |
| Entry price 1ct G-VS2 | $2,887 | $3,150 |

