### Pear Settings: V-Prong Mandatory

A pear's pointed tip is the thinnest section of any popular diamond shape. Standard round prongs placed near the tip provide inadequate contact with the narrowing girdle and leave the tip exposed to chipping from lateral impact against hard surfaces (countertops, door frames, gym equipment).

**The V-prong requirement:** A V-prong is a single prong bent into a V-shape that cups both sides of the tip, distributing any impact force across two contact points rather than leaving the narrowest section of the stone exposed. Confirm the setting uses a V-prong before purchasing — if the description only says "prong setting" without specifying V-tip at the point, ask.

